I'm seeing a strange issue where a masked display object changes color. See the following screenshot. The Quad on the left is not masked, and the Quad on the right is masked by a red Quad.

![mask-color-issue](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/141885/12308153/73419ea4-b9f8-11e5-898a-87b413b57415.png)

Here's the code:

```
var quad1:Quad = new Quad(100, 100, 0x999999);
quad1.x = 20;
quad1.y = 20;
this.addChild(quad1);

var quad2:Quad = new Quad(100, 100, 0x999999);
quad2.x = 140;
quad2.y = 20;
this.addChild(quad2);

var mask:Quad = new Quad(100, 100, 0xff0000);
quad2.mask = mask;
```

Interestingly, if you change the color of the mask quad, the discoloration changes to match. It's like the mask is rendering at a very small alpha value that is just slightly larger than 0.
